cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category because it deals with image analysis and segmentation using Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) scans. The use of deep learning and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on improving performance and addressing class imbalance could also place it in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of MRI scans for medical diagnosis could suggest that it belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with information extraction and retrieval from medical records.
